```

### If Backfill Fails

1. Stop the backfill process
2. Identify which partitions were modified
3. Restore from backup/snapshot
4. Verify restoration with validation queries
5. Investigate root cause before retrying

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It's Bad | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|------------------|
| Non-idempotent writes | Duplicate data on retry | Upsert or replace semantics |
| No progress tracking | Can't resume after failure | Checkpoint after each batch |
| No validation | Silent data corruption | Validate every batch |
| Competing with live pipeline | Resource contention | Schedule during off-peak |
